I could not figure out `o(n)` approach on my own. 
I needed to read at least 3 solution by really brilliant people (top voted) to understand the approach.
Then I had to do the math on pen-paper 3 times (made mistake 2 time) to actually understand the approach.
Then when I actually started coding, I made some some silly mistakes around Stack boundry and 
the cherry on top was that you need to do `+ mod) % mod` at almost every place you are doing any calculation.

Overall, very good learning experience but I really pity the ones who actually face this in interview.

Run time complexity: `4 * O(n)` =  `O(n)` 
Space compexity: `O(n)`

